parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine compartment fires can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. In extreme cases, fires can spread to other parts of the vehicle, causing a total loss.
symptoms: Rattling noise from the front of the car
and a hole in the engine block.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Exhaust system failures can cause noise, vibration, and potentially lead to fires or damage to other components.
The failure of the differential unit can cause the vehicle to come to a sudden stop, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: no warning of low fluid in the differential unit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to seize or lock up, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: the vehicle comes to a sudden stop
the transmission problem is confirmed by the dealer.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift interlock can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: The key can be removed in any gear
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
the vehicle hits a parked vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle shaft can cause the vehicle to lose control or become unstable, increasing the risk of accidents or collisions.
symptoms: the vehicle loses control or becomes unstable.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Grinding and Extended Stopping Distance
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The grinding of brakes can cause extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents and potentially leading to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Grinding noise when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adjustable foot pedal can lead to accidental acceleration or braking, causing accidents and potentially resulting in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Difficulty distinguishing between the accelerator and brake pedals

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake drum can cause a loss of brake performance, leading to extended stopping distances and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A post-ignition fire can cause significant damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a total loss, and posing a risk to the safety of occupants and bystanders.
symptoms: The vehicle catches on fire under the hood
usually after the engine has been turned off

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical Short Circuit due to Gearshift Wire Rubbing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short circuit can cause a fire, damage to the vehicle's electrical system, and potentially lead to a loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: sparks or smoke from the gearshift area
